(531, '_transient_dash_4077549d03da2e451c8b5f002294ff51', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''https://wordpress.org/news/2014/12/wordpress-4-1-release-candidate-3/''>WordPress 4.1 Release Candidate 3</a> <span class="rss-date">December 18, 2014</span><div class="rssSummary">The next release candidate for WordPress 4.1 is now available for testing. Seventy changes have gone in since the first release candidate. With no known issues left, we plan to release 4.1 tomorrow, December 18. To test, try the WordPress Beta Tester plugin (you’ll want “bleeding edge nightlies”). Or you can download the release candidate here (zip). If you’d like to learn more about [&hellip;]</div></li></ul></div><div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/intergalactic-a-bold-free-wordpress-theme-from-automattic''>WPTavern: Intergalactic: A Bold Free WordPress Theme from Automattic</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/how-to-take-control-of-the-wordpress-heartbeat-api''>WPTavern: How to Take Control of The WordPress Heartbeat API</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wptavern.com/atlanta-wordpress-coders-guild-a-new-meetup-for-designers-and-programmers''>WPTavern: Atlanta WordPress Coders Guild: A New Meetup for Designers and Programmers</a></li></ul></div><div class="rss-widget"><ul><li class=''dashboard-news-plugin''><span>Popular Plugin:</span> <a href=''https://wordpress.org/plugins/jetpack/'' class=''dashboard-news-plugin-link''>Jetpack by WordPress.com</a>&nbsp;<span>(<a href=''plugin-install.php?tab=plugin-information&amp;plugin=jetpack&amp;_wpnonce=e870eb9343&amp;TB_iframe=true&amp;width=600&amp;height=800'' class=''thickbox'' title=''Jetpack by WordPress.com''>Install</a>)</span></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
